Description: p2-raw-in-vault — document _raw as configurable, not in-vault
 Audit p2 (docs/260418-dual-sensitivity-analysis.md §5.4) flags several
 locations that state `_raw/` lives "inside your vault" — misleading in
 dual-zone deployments where the staging directory is set via
 `OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR` to a path outside `$OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH`.
 .
 Severity : TROMPEUR. Skills still work (they resolve the path via the
 env var anyway) but the documentation lies about the layout contract.
 .
 Targets in this patch (4) :
   - AGENTS.md line 24 (vault-structure tree)
   - .env.example line 49 (comment block for OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR)
   - README.md line 220 (`_raw/` Staging Directory section)
   - .skills/wiki-setup/SKILL.md line 45 (staging area description)
 .
 Deliberately excluded :
   - `.skills/wiki-ingest/SKILL.md` (lines 58-62) — already rewritten
     by B1 (`b1-wiki-ingest-raw-fallback`, order 1). Strategy (b) from
     jalon-15 spec : avoid hunk overlap by letting B1 own that file ;
     the new wording from B1 ("`OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR` (required, must be
     absolute)") already conveys the same "not-in-vault" message.
   - `.env` — gitignored ; the offending wording there is subsumed by
     B3 (blanks OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH) and by B4 (obsolete record).
     Touching `.env` here would require another runtime.json override
     and add no semantic gain.
 .
 Wording : "(configured via OBSIDIAN_RAW_DIR; may live outside the
 vault in dual-zone setups)" — short enough to stay on one line in the
 tree diagrams, explicit enough to correct the mental model.
Origin: local
Bug-Ref: docs/260418-dual-sensitivity-analysis.md §5.4
Forwarded: no
